Aux:TextAnnotations.Aux:document_text: INDIANA STATE DEPARTMENT OF AGRICULTURE DIVISION OF SOIL CONSERVATION CLEAN WATER INDIANA (CWI) WATERSHED GRANT PROGRAM EDS # A337-12-CWL015 Amendment # 1 This is an amendment to the Grant Agreement entered into by and between the Indiana Slate Department of Agriculture, Division of Soil Conservation (the “’State’') and Johnson County Soil and Water Conservation District (the “Grantee”) dated December 20, 2011. In consideration of the mutual undertakings and covenants hereinafter set forth, the parties agree as follows: The Grant Agreement is hereby extended for an additional period of one year. It shall terminate on December 31, 2014. The Grant Agreement is hereby increased in amount by $20,000.00. Total remuneration under this Grant Agreement shall not exceed $60,000.00. These funds shall be used to further continue the project described in Exhibit A of the original agreement. All other matters previously agreed to and set forth in the original Grant Agreement and not affected by this Amendment shall remain in full force and effect. Non-Collnsion and Acceptance The undersigned attests, subject to the penalties for petjury, that he/she is the Grantee, or that he/she is the representative, agent, member or officer of the Grantee, that he/she has not, nor has any other member, employee, representative, agent or officer of the Grantee, directly or indirectly, to the best of his/her knowledge, entered into or offered to enter into any combination, collusion or agreement to receive or pay, and that he/she has not received or paid any sum of money or other consideration for the execution of this Amendment, other than that which appears on the face hereof. . The remainder of this page is left blank intentionally.
